cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM

This paper deals with deep generative models for visual objects, specifically focusing on disentangling the latent characteristics of appearance and pose. This makes it highly relevant to computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also proposes a novel approach for regularization, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper deals with image synthesis and modification, which could be relevant to graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
